  "title": "Mynocks, Mayhem, and a Murderous Astromech",
  "summary": "Aboard Johanna Damion's flagship, the Price of Pleasure, a mynock infestation brought in on a careless pilot's cargo shuttle throws the main hangar into chaos. The drunken captain Johanna laments her ruined ship while her broker Ecks frantically tallies the mounting repair costs and her homicidal astromech Cricket gleefully hunts the last mynock, tasering the newly arrived liaison officer Galen Rourke in the process. Physician Lynae Cassius arrives to find old acquaintance Rourke, who, after a disastrous day, impulsively kisses her, prompting her to flip him to the deck before kissing him back. The scene devolves into comic disaster as Johanna vomits on Ecks's custom boots and Cricket tries to eat the foam-covered mynock. No real resolution is reached, the log ending mid-chaos as a comedic ensemble piece introducing Rourke to the crew.",
